4/*
5 When the active program changes, we need to update it's uniforms.
6 We could track state for each program and only update stale uniforms
7 - Could lead to lots of overhead if there's a lot of programs
8 We could update all the uniforms when the program changes
9 - Could end up updating lots of uniforms which don't need updating
10
11 Updating uniforms should be cheap, so the overhead of updating up-to-date
12 uniforms should be minimal. It's also less complex.
13
14 Things which _may_ cause a different program to be used:
15 - Change in brush/pen style
16 - Change in painter opacity
17 - Change in composition mode
18
19 Whenever we set a mode on the shader manager - it needs to tell us if it had
20 to switch to a different program.
21
22 The shader manager should only switch when we tell it to. E.g. if we set a new
23 brush style and then switch to transparent painter, we only want it to compile
24 and use the correct program when we really need it.
25*/
26

83QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::~QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate()
84{
85 delete shaderManager;
86
87 vertexBuffer.destroy();
88 texCoordBuffer.destroy();
89 opacityBuffer.destroy();
90 indexBuffer.destroy();
91 vao.destroy();
92

94 funcs.glDeleteBuffers(n: 1, buffers: &elementIndicesVBOId);
95 elementIndicesVBOId = 0;
96 }
97}

99inline QColor qt_premultiplyColor(QColor c, GLfloat opacity)
100{
101 qreal alpha = c.alphaF() * opacity;
102 c.setAlphaF(alpha);
103 c.setRedF(c.redF() * alpha);
104 c.setGreenF(c.greenF() * alpha);
105 c.setBlueF(c.blueF() * alpha);
106 return c;
107}

110void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::setBrush(const QBrush& brush)
111{
112 if (qbrush_fast_equals(a: currentBrush, b: brush))
113 return;
114
115 const Qt::BrushStyle newStyle = qbrush_style(b: brush);
116 Q_ASSERT(newStyle != Qt::NoBrush);
117
118 currentBrush = brush;
119 if (!currentBrushImage.isNull())
120 currentBrushImage = QImage();
121 brushUniformsDirty = true; // All brushes have at least one uniform
122
123 if (newStyle > Qt::SolidPattern)
124 brushTextureDirty = true;
125
126 if (currentBrush.style() == Qt::TexturePattern
127 && qHasPixmapTexture(brush) && brush.texture().isQBitmap())
128 {
129 shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::TextureSrcWithPattern);
130 } else {
131 shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(newStyle);
132 }
133 shaderManager->optimiseForBrushTransform(transformType: currentBrush.transform().type());
134}

145/*
146 Single entry-point for activating, binding, and setting properties.
147
148 Allows keeping track of (caching) the latest texture unit and bound
149 texture in a central place, so that we can skip re-binding unless
150 needed.
151
152 \note Any code or Qt API that internally activates or binds will
153 not affect the cache used by this function, which means they will
154 lead to inconsistent state. QPainter::beginNativePainting() takes
155 care of resetting the cache, so for user–code this is fine, but
156 internally in the paint engine care must be taken to not call
157 functions that may activate or bind under our feet.
158*/
159template<typename T>
160void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateTexture(GLenum textureUnit, const T &texture, GLenum wrapMode, GLenum filterMode, TextureUpdateMode updateMode)
161{
162 static const GLenum target = GL_TEXTURE_2D;
163
164 activateTextureUnit(textureUnit);
165
166 GLuint textureId = bindTexture(texture);
167
168 if (updateMode == UpdateIfNeeded && textureId == lastTextureUsed)
169 return;
170
171 lastTextureUsed = textureId;
172
173 funcs.glTexParameteri(target, GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S, param: wrapMode);
174 funcs.glTexParameteri(target, GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T, param: wrapMode);
175
176 funcs.glTexParameteri(target, GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER, param: filterMode);
177 funcs.glTexParameteri(target, GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, param: filterMode);
178}
179
180void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::activateTextureUnit(GLenum textureUnit)
181{
182 if (textureUnit != lastTextureUnitUsed) {
183 funcs.glActiveTexture(GL_TEXTURE0 + textureUnit);
184 lastTextureUnitUsed = textureUnit;
185
186 // We simplify things by keeping a single cached value of the last
187 // texture that was bound, instead of one per texture unit. This
188 // means that switching texture units could potentially mean we
189 // need a re-bind and corresponding parameter updates.
190 lastTextureUsed = GLuint(-1);
191 }
192}
193
194template<>
195GLuint QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::bindTexture(const GLuint &textureId)
196{
197 if (textureId != lastTextureUsed)
198 funcs.glBindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, texture: textureId);
199
200 return textureId;
201}

214
215template<>
216GLuint QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::bindTexture(const QGradient &gradient)
217{
218 // We apply global opacity in the fragment shaders, so we always pass 1.0
219 // for opacity to the cache.
220 GLuint textureId = QOpenGL2GradientCache::cacheForContext(context: ctx)->getBuffer(gradient, opacity: 1.0);
221
222 // QOpenGL2GradientCache::getBuffer() may bind and generate a new texture if it
223 // hasn't been cached yet, but will otherwise return an unbound texture id. To
224 // be sure that the texture is bound, we unfortunately have to bind again,
225 // which results in the initial generation of the texture doing two binds.
226 return bindTexture(textureId);
227}

241inline static bool isPowerOfTwo(int x)
242{
243 // Assumption: x >= 1
244 return x == (x & -x);
245}
246
247void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateBrushTexture()
248{
249 Q_Q(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
250// qDebug("QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateBrushTexture()");
251 Qt::BrushStyle style = currentBrush.style();
252
253 bool smoothPixmapTransform = q->state()->renderHints & QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform;
254 GLenum filterMode = smoothPixmapTransform ? GL_LINEAR : GL_NEAREST;
255
256 if ( (style >= Qt::Dense1Pattern) && (style <= Qt::DiagCrossPattern) ) {
257 // Get the image data for the pattern
258 QImage textureImage = qt_imageForBrush(brushStyle: style, invert: false);
259
260 updateTexture(QT_BRUSH_TEXTURE_UNIT, texture: textureImage, GL_REPEAT, filterMode, updateMode: ForceUpdate);
261 }
262 else if (style >= Qt::LinearGradientPattern && style <= Qt::ConicalGradientPattern) {
263 // Gradiant brush: All the gradiants use the same texture
264
265 const QGradient *gradient = currentBrush.gradient();
266
267 GLenum wrapMode = GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE;
268 if (gradient->spread() == QGradient::RepeatSpread || gradient->type() == QGradient::ConicalGradient)
269 wrapMode = GL_REPEAT;
270 else if (gradient->spread() == QGradient::ReflectSpread)
271 wrapMode = GL_MIRRORED_REPEAT;
272
273 updateTexture(QT_BRUSH_TEXTURE_UNIT, texture: *gradient, wrapMode, filterMode, updateMode: ForceUpdate);
274 }
275 else if (style == Qt::TexturePattern) {
276 currentBrushImage = currentBrush.textureImage();
277
278 int max_texture_size = ctx->d_func()->maxTextureSize();
279 QSize newSize = currentBrushImage.size();
280 newSize = newSize.boundedTo(otherSize: QSize(max_texture_size, max_texture_size));
281 if (!QOpenGLContext::currentContext()->functions()->hasOpenGLFeature(feature: QOpenGLFunctions::NPOTTextureRepeat)) {
282 if (!isPowerOfTwo(x: newSize.width()) || !isPowerOfTwo(x: newSize.height())) {
283 newSize.setHeight(qNextPowerOfTwo(v: newSize.height() - 1));
284 newSize.setWidth(qNextPowerOfTwo(v: newSize.width() - 1));
285 }
286 }
287 if (currentBrushImage.size() != newSize)
288 currentBrushImage = currentBrushImage.scaled(s: newSize, aspectMode: Qt::IgnoreAspectRatio, mode: Qt::SmoothTransformation);
289
290 GLuint wrapMode = GL_REPEAT;
291
292 updateTexture(QT_BRUSH_TEXTURE_UNIT, texture: currentBrushImage, wrapMode, filterMode, updateMode: ForceUpdate);
293 }
294 brushTextureDirty = false;
295}

298void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateBrushUniforms()
299{
300// qDebug("QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateBrushUniforms()");
301 Qt::BrushStyle style = currentBrush.style();
302
303 if (style == Qt::NoBrush)
304 return;
305
306 QTransform brushQTransform = currentBrush.transform();
307 bool isCosmetic = false;
308
309 if (style == Qt::SolidPattern) {
310 QColor col = qt_premultiplyColor(c: currentBrush.color(), opacity: (GLfloat)q->state()->opacity);
311 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::FragmentColor), color: col);
312 }
313 else {
314 // All other brushes have a transform and thus need the translation point:
315 QPointF translationPoint;
316
317 if (style <= Qt::DiagCrossPattern) {
318 QColor col = qt_premultiplyColor(c: currentBrush.color(), opacity: (GLfloat)q->state()->opacity);
319
320 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::PatternColor), color: col);
321
322 QVector2D halfViewportSize(width*0.5, height*0.5);
323 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::HalfViewportSize), value: halfViewportSize);
324
325 isCosmetic = !q->painter()->testRenderHint(hint: QPainter::NonCosmeticBrushPatterns);
326 }
327 else if (style == Qt::LinearGradientPattern) {
328 const QLinearGradient *g = static_cast<const QLinearGradient *>(currentBrush.gradient());
329
330 QPointF realStart = g->start();
331 QPointF realFinal = g->finalStop();
332 translationPoint = realStart;
333
334 QPointF l = realFinal - realStart;
335
336 QVector3D linearData(
337 l.x(),
338 l.y(),
339 1.0f / (l.x() * l.x() + l.y() * l.y())
340 );
341
342 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::LinearData), value: linearData);
343
344 QVector2D halfViewportSize(width*0.5, height*0.5);
345 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::HalfViewportSize), value: halfViewportSize);
346 }
347 else if (style == Qt::ConicalGradientPattern) {
348 const QConicalGradient *g = static_cast<const QConicalGradient *>(currentBrush.gradient());
349 translationPoint = g->center();
350
351 GLfloat angle = -qDegreesToRadians(degrees: g->angle());
352
353 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::Angle), value: angle);
354
355 QVector2D halfViewportSize(width*0.5, height*0.5);
356 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::HalfViewportSize), value: halfViewportSize);
357 }
358 else if (style == Qt::RadialGradientPattern) {
359 const QRadialGradient *g = static_cast<const QRadialGradient *>(currentBrush.gradient());
360 QPointF realCenter = g->center();
361 QPointF realFocal = g->focalPoint();
362 qreal realRadius = g->centerRadius() - g->focalRadius();
363 translationPoint = realFocal;
364
365 QPointF fmp = realCenter - realFocal;
366 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::Fmp), point: fmp);
367
368 GLfloat fmp2_m_radius2 = -fmp.x() * fmp.x() - fmp.y() * fmp.y() + realRadius*realRadius;
369 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::Fmp2MRadius2), value: fmp2_m_radius2);
370 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::Inverse2Fmp2MRadius2),
371 value: GLfloat(1.0 / (2.0*fmp2_m_radius2)));
372 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::SqrFr),
373 value: GLfloat(g->focalRadius() * g->focalRadius()));
374 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::BRadius),
375 x: GLfloat(2 * (g->centerRadius() - g->focalRadius()) * g->focalRadius()),
376 y: g->focalRadius(),
377 z: g->centerRadius() - g->focalRadius());
378
379 QVector2D halfViewportSize(width*0.5, height*0.5);
380 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::HalfViewportSize), value: halfViewportSize);
381 }
382 else if (style == Qt::TexturePattern) {
383 const QPixmap& texPixmap = currentBrush.texture();
384
385 if (qHasPixmapTexture(brush: currentBrush) && currentBrush.texture().isQBitmap()) {
386 QColor col = qt_premultiplyColor(c: currentBrush.color(), opacity: (GLfloat)q->state()->opacity);
387 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::PatternColor), color: col);
388 }
389
390 QSizeF invertedTextureSize(1.0 / texPixmap.width(), 1.0 / texPixmap.height());
391 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::InvertedTextureSize), size: invertedTextureSize);
392
393 QVector2D halfViewportSize(width*0.5, height*0.5);
394 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::HalfViewportSize), value: halfViewportSize);
395 }
396 else
397 qWarning(msg: "QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx: Unimplemented fill style");
398
399 const QPointF &brushOrigin = q->state()->brushOrigin;
400 QTransform matrix;
401 if (!isCosmetic)
402 matrix = q->state()->matrix;
403 matrix.translate(dx: brushOrigin.x(), dy: brushOrigin.y());
404 if (!isCosmetic)
405 matrix = brushQTransform * matrix;
406
407 QTransform translate(1, 0, 0, 1, -translationPoint.x(), -translationPoint.y());
408 qreal m22 = -1;
409 qreal dy = height;
410 if (device->paintFlipped()) {
411 m22 = 1;
412 dy = 0;
413 }
414 QTransform gl_to_qt(1, 0, 0, m22, 0, dy);
415 QTransform inv_matrix = gl_to_qt * matrix.inverted() * translate;
416
417 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::BrushTransform), value: inv_matrix);
418 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::BrushTexture), QT_BRUSH_TEXTURE_UNIT);
419 }
420 brushUniformsDirty = false;
421}

424// This assumes the shader manager has already setup the correct shader program
425void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateMatrix()
426{
427// qDebug("QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateMatrix()");
428
429 const QTransform& transform = q->state()->matrix;
430
431 // The projection matrix converts from Qt's coordinate system to GL's coordinate system
432 // * GL's viewport is 2x2, Qt's is width x height
433 // * GL has +y -> -y going from bottom -> top, Qt is the other way round
434 // * GL has [0,0] in the center, Qt has it in the top-left
435 //
436 // This results in the Projection matrix below, which is multiplied by the painter's
437 // transformation matrix, as shown below:
438 //
439 // Projection Matrix Painter Transform
440 // ------------------------------------------------ ------------------------
441 // | 2.0 / width | 0.0 | -1.0 | | m11 | m21 | dx |
442 // | 0.0 | -2.0 / height | 1.0 | * | m12 | m22 | dy |
443 // | 0.0 | 0.0 | 1.0 | | m13 | m23 | m33 |
444 // ------------------------------------------------ ------------------------
445 //
446 // NOTE: The resultant matrix is also transposed, as GL expects column-major matracies
447
448 const GLfloat wfactor = 2.0f / width;
449 GLfloat hfactor = -2.0f / height;
450
451 GLfloat dx = transform.dx();
452 GLfloat dy = transform.dy();
453
454 if (device->paintFlipped()) {
455 hfactor *= -1;
456 dy -= height;
457 }
458
459 // Non-integer translates can have strange effects for some rendering operations such as
460 // anti-aliased text rendering. In such cases, we snap the translate to the pixel grid.
461 if (snapToPixelGrid && transform.type() == QTransform::TxTranslate) {
462 // 0.50 needs to rounded down to 0.0 for consistency with raster engine:
463 dx = std::ceil(x: dx - 0.5f);
464 dy = std::ceil(x: dy - 0.5f);
465 }
466 pmvMatrix[0][0] = (wfactor * transform.m11()) - transform.m13();
467 pmvMatrix[1][0] = (wfactor * transform.m21()) - transform.m23();
468 pmvMatrix[2][0] = (wfactor * dx) - transform.m33();
469 pmvMatrix[0][1] = (hfactor * transform.m12()) + transform.m13();
470 pmvMatrix[1][1] = (hfactor * transform.m22()) + transform.m23();
471 pmvMatrix[2][1] = (hfactor * dy) + transform.m33();
472 pmvMatrix[0][2] = transform.m13();
473 pmvMatrix[1][2] = transform.m23();
474 pmvMatrix[2][2] = transform.m33();
475
476 // 1/10000 == 0.0001, so we have good enough res to cover curves
477 // that span the entire widget...
478 inverseScale = qMax(a: 1 / qMax( a: qMax(a: qAbs(t: transform.m11()), b: qAbs(t: transform.m22())),
479 b: qMax(a: qAbs(t: transform.m12()), b: qAbs(t: transform.m21())) ),
480 b: qreal(0.0001));
481
482 matrixDirty = false;
483 matrixUniformDirty = true;
484
485 // Set the PMV matrix attribute. As we use an attributes rather than uniforms, we only
486 // need to do this once for every matrix change and persists across all shader programs.
487 funcs.glVertexAttrib3fv(indx: QT_PMV_MATRIX_1_ATTR, values: pmvMatrix[0]);
488 funcs.glVertexAttrib3fv(indx: QT_PMV_MATRIX_2_ATTR, values: pmvMatrix[1]);
489 funcs.glVertexAttrib3fv(indx: QT_PMV_MATRIX_3_ATTR, values: pmvMatrix[2]);
490
491 dasher.setInvScale(inverseScale);
492 stroker.setInvScale(inverseScale);
493}

496void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateCompositionMode()
497{
498 // NOTE: The entire paint engine works on pre-multiplied data - which is why some of these
499 // composition modes look odd.
500// qDebug() << "QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateCompositionMode() - Setting GL composition mode for " << q->state()->composition_mode;
501 if (ctx->functions()->hasOpenGLFeature(feature: QOpenGLFunctions::BlendEquationAdvanced)) {
502 if (q->state()->composition_mode <= QPainter::CompositionMode_Plus) {
503 funcs.glDisable(GL_BLEND_ADVANCED_COHERENT_KHR);
504 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_FUNC_ADD);
505 } else {
506 funcs.glEnable(GL_BLEND_ADVANCED_COHERENT_KHR);
507 }
508 shaderManager->setCompositionMode(q->state()->composition_mode);
509 } else {
510 if (q->state()->composition_mode > QPainter::CompositionMode_Plus) {
511 qWarning(msg: "Unsupported composition mode");
512 compositionModeDirty = false;
513 return;
514 }
515 }
516 switch(q->state()->composition_mode) {
517 case QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver:
518 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA);
519 break;
520 case QPainter::CompositionMode_DestinationOver:
521 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA, GL_ONE);
522 break;
523 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Clear:
524 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ZERO, GL_ZERO);
525 break;
526 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Source:
527 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE, GL_ZERO);
528 break;
529 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Destination:
530 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ZERO, GL_ONE);
531 break;
532 case QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceIn:
533 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_DST_ALPHA, GL_ZERO);
534 break;
535 case QPainter::CompositionMode_DestinationIn:
536 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ZERO, GL_SRC_ALPHA);
537 break;
538 case QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOut:
539 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA, GL_ZERO);
540 break;
541 case QPainter::CompositionMode_DestinationOut:
542 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ZERO, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA);
543 break;
544 case QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceAtop:
545 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_DST_ALPHA, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA);
546 break;
547 case QPainter::CompositionMode_DestinationAtop:
548 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA, GL_SRC_ALPHA);
549 break;
550 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Xor:
551 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA);
552 break;
553 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Plus:
554 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE, GL_ONE);
555 break;
556 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Multiply:
557 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_MULTIPLY_KHR);
558 break;
559 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Screen:
560 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_SCREEN_KHR);
561 break;
562 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Overlay:
563 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_OVERLAY_KHR);
564 break;
565 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Darken:
566 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_DARKEN_KHR);
567 break;
568 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Lighten:
569 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_LIGHTEN_KHR);
570 break;
571 case QPainter::CompositionMode_ColorDodge:
572 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_COLORDODGE_KHR);
573 break;
574 case QPainter::CompositionMode_ColorBurn:
575 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_COLORBURN_KHR);
576 break;
577 case QPainter::CompositionMode_HardLight:
578 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_HARDLIGHT_KHR);
579 break;
580 case QPainter::CompositionMode_SoftLight:
581 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_SOFTLIGHT_KHR);
582 break;
583 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Difference:
584 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_DIFFERENCE_KHR);
585 break;
586 case QPainter::CompositionMode_Exclusion:
587 funcs.glBlendEquation(GL_EXCLUSION_KHR);
588 break;
589 default:
590 qWarning(msg: "Unsupported composition mode");
591 break;
592 }
593
594 compositionModeDirty = false;
595}

597static inline void setCoords(GLfloat *coords, const QOpenGLRect &rect)
598{
599 coords[0] = rect.left;
600 coords[1] = rect.top;
601 coords[2] = rect.right;
602 coords[3] = rect.top;
603 coords[4] = rect.right;
604 coords[5] = rect.bottom;
605 coords[6] = rect.left;
606 coords[7] = rect.bottom;
607}

609void Q_TRACE_INSTRUMENT(qtopengl) QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::drawTexture(const QOpenGLRect& dest, const QOpenGLRect& src, const QSize &textureSize, bool opaque, bool pattern)
610{
611 Q_TRACE_PARAM_REPLACE(QOpenGLRect, QRectF);
612 Q_TRACE_SCOPE(QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate_drawTexture, dest, src, textureSize, opaque, pattern);
613
614 // Setup for texture drawing
615 currentBrush = noBrush;
616
617 if (snapToPixelGrid) {
618 snapToPixelGrid = false;
619 matrixDirty = true;
620 }
621
622 if (prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: opaque))
623 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageTexture), QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT);
624
625 if (pattern) {
626 QColor col = qt_premultiplyColor(c: q->state()->pen.color(), opacity: (GLfloat)q->state()->opacity);
627 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::PatternColor), color: col);
628 }
629
630 GLfloat dx = 1.0 / textureSize.width();
631 GLfloat dy = 1.0 / textureSize.height();
632
633 QOpenGLRect srcTextureRect(src.left*dx, src.top*dy, src.right*dx, src.bottom*dy);
634
635 setCoords(coords: staticVertexCoordinateArray, rect: dest);
636 setCoords(coords: staticTextureCoordinateArray, rect: srcTextureRect);
637
638 setVertexAttribArrayEnabled(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, enabled: true);
639 setVertexAttribArrayEnabled(arrayIndex: QT_TEXTURE_COORDS_ATTR, enabled: true);
640
641 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: staticVertexCoordinateArray, count: 8);
642 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_TEXTURE_COORDS_ATTR, data: staticTextureCoordinateArray, count: 8);
643
644 funcs.glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLE_FAN, first: 0, count: 4);
645}

647void QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::beginNativePainting()
648{
649 Q_D(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
650 ensureActive();
651 d->transferMode(newMode: BrushDrawingMode);
652
653 d->nativePaintingActive = true;
654
655 d->funcs.glUseProgram(program: 0);
656
657 // Disable all the vertex attribute arrays:
658 for (int i = 0; i < QT_GL_VERTEX_ARRAY_TRACKED_COUNT; ++i)
659 d->funcs.glDisableVertexAttribArray(index: i);
660
661#if !QT_CONFIG(opengles2) && !defined(QT_OPENGL_DYNAMIC)
662 Q_ASSERT(QOpenGLContext::currentContext());
663 const QOpenGLContext *ctx = d->ctx;
664 const QSurfaceFormat &fmt = d->device->context()->format();
665 if (fmt.majorVersion() < 3 || (fmt.majorVersion() == 3 && fmt.minorVersion() < 1)
666 || (fmt.majorVersion() == 3 && fmt.minorVersion() == 1 && ctx->hasExtension(QByteArrayLiteral("GL_ARB_compatibility")))
667 || fmt.profile() == QSurfaceFormat::CompatibilityProfile)
668 {
669 // be nice to people who mix OpenGL 1.x code with QPainter commands
670 // by setting modelview and projection matrices to mirror the GL 1
671 // paint engine
672 const QTransform& mtx = state()->matrix;
673
674 float mv_matrix[4][4] =
675 {
676 { float(mtx.m11()), float(mtx.m12()), 0, float(mtx.m13()) },
677 { float(mtx.m21()), float(mtx.m22()), 0, float(mtx.m23()) },
678 { 0, 0, 1, 0 },
679 { float(mtx.dx()), float(mtx.dy()), 0, float(mtx.m33()) }
680 };
681
682 const QSize sz = d->device->size();
683
684 glMatrixMode(GL_PROJECTION);
685 glLoadIdentity();
686 glOrtho(left: 0, right: sz.width(), bottom: sz.height(), top: 0, near_val: -999999, far_val: 999999);
687
688 glMatrixMode(GL_MODELVIEW);
689 glLoadMatrixf(m: &mv_matrix[0][0]);
690 }
691#endif // !QT_CONFIG(opengles2)
692
693 d->resetGLState();
694
695 // We don't know what texture units and textures the native painting
696 // will activate and bind, so we can't assume anything when we return
697 // from the native painting.
698 d->lastTextureUnitUsed = QT_UNKNOWN_TEXTURE_UNIT;
699 d->lastTextureUsed = GLuint(-1);
700
701 d->dirtyStencilRegion = QRect(0, 0, d->width, d->height);
702
703 d->shaderManager->setDirty();
704
705 d->needsSync = true;
706}

708void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::resetGLState()
709{
710 activateTextureUnit(QT_DEFAULT_TEXTURE_UNIT);
711
712 funcs.glDisable(GL_BLEND);
713 funcs.glDisable(GL_STENCIL_TEST);
714 funcs.glDisable(GL_DEPTH_TEST);
715 funcs.glDisable(GL_SCISSOR_TEST);
716 funcs.glDepthMask(flag: true);
717 funcs.glDepthFunc(GL_LESS);
718 funcs.glClearDepthf(depth: 1);
719 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0xff);
720 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_KEEP, GL_KEEP);
721 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_ALWAYS, ref: 0, mask: 0xff);
722 setVertexAttribArrayEnabled(arrayIndex: QT_TEXTURE_COORDS_ATTR, enabled: false);
723 setVertexAttribArrayEnabled(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, enabled: false);
724 setVertexAttribArrayEnabled(arrayIndex: QT_OPACITY_ATTR, enabled: false);
725 if (!QOpenGLContext::currentContext()->isOpenGLES()) {
726 // gl_Color, corresponding to vertex attribute 3, may have been changed
727 float color[] = { 1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f };
728 funcs.glVertexAttrib4fv(indx: 3, values: color);
729 }
730 if (vao.isCreated())
731 vao.release();
732
733 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, buffer: 0);
734 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, buffer: 0);
735}

755void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::transferMode(EngineMode newMode)
756{
757 if (newMode == mode)
758 return;
759
760 if (newMode == TextDrawingMode) {
761 shaderManager->setHasComplexGeometry(true);
762 } else {
763 shaderManager->setHasComplexGeometry(false);
764 }
765
766 if (newMode == ImageDrawingMode) {
767 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: staticVertexCoordinateArray, count: 8);
768 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_TEXTURE_COORDS_ATTR, data: staticTextureCoordinateArray, count: 8);
769 }
770
771 if (newMode == ImageArrayDrawingMode || newMode == ImageOpacityArrayDrawingMode) {
772 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)vertexCoordinateArray.data(), count: vertexCoordinateArray.vertexCount() * 2);
773 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_TEXTURE_COORDS_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)textureCoordinateArray.data(), count: textureCoordinateArray.vertexCount() * 2);
774
775 if (newMode == ImageOpacityArrayDrawingMode)
776 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_OPACITY_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)opacityArray.data(), count: opacityArray.size());
777 }
778
779 // This needs to change when we implement high-quality anti-aliasing...
780 if (newMode != TextDrawingMode)
781 shaderManager->setMaskType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::NoMask);
782
783 mode = newMode;
784}

786struct QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache
787{
788#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
789 GLuint vbo;
790 GLuint ibo;
791#else
792 float *vertices;
793 void *indices;
794#endif
795 int vertexCount;
796 int indexCount;
797 GLenum primitiveType;
798 qreal iscale;
799 QVertexIndexVector::Type indexType;
800};

802void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::cleanupVectorPath(QPaintEngineEx *engine, void *data)
803{
804 QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache *c = (QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache *) data;
805#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
806 Q_ASSERT(engine->type() == QPaintEngine::OpenGL2);
807 static_cast<QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx *>(engine)->d_func()->unusedVBOSToClean << c->vbo;
808 if (c->ibo)
809 d->unusedIBOSToClean << c->ibo;
810#else
811 Q_UNUSED(engine);
812 free(ptr: c->vertices);
813 free(ptr: c->indices);
814#endif
815 delete c;
816}
817
818// Assumes everything is configured for the brush you want to use
819void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::fill(const QVectorPath& path)
820{
821 transferMode(newMode: BrushDrawingMode);
822
823 if (snapToPixelGrid) {
824 snapToPixelGrid = false;
825 matrixDirty = true;
826 }
827
828 // Might need to call updateMatrix to re-calculate inverseScale
829 if (matrixDirty) {
830 updateMatrix();
831 if (currentBrush.style() > Qt::SolidPattern)
832 brushUniformsDirty = true;
833 }
834
835 const bool supportsElementIndexUint = funcs.hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::ElementIndexUint);
836
837 const QPointF* const points = reinterpret_cast<const QPointF*>(path.points());
838
839 // Check to see if there's any hints
840 if (path.shape() == QVectorPath::RectangleHint) {
841 QOpenGLRect rect(points[0].x(), points[0].y(), points[2].x(), points[2].y());
842 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: currentBrush.isOpaque());
843 composite(boundingRect: rect);
844 } else if (path.isConvex()) {
845
846 if (path.isCacheable()) {
847 QVectorPath::CacheEntry *data = path.lookupCacheData(engine: q);
848 QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache *cache;
849
850 bool updateCache = false;
851
852 if (data) {
853 cache = (QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache *) data->data;
854 // Check if scale factor is exceeded and regenerate if so...
855 qreal scaleFactor = cache->iscale / inverseScale;
856 if (scaleFactor < 0.5 || scaleFactor > 2.0) {
857#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
858 glDeleteBuffers(1, &cache->vbo);
859 cache->vbo = 0;
860 Q_ASSERT(cache->ibo == 0);
861#else
862 free(ptr: cache->vertices);
863 Q_ASSERT(cache->indices == nullptr);
864#endif
865 updateCache = true;
866 }
867 } else {
868 cache = new QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache;
869 data = const_cast<QVectorPath &>(path).addCacheData(engine: q, data: cache, cleanup: cleanupVectorPath);
870 updateCache = true;
871 }
872
873 // Flatten the path at the current scale factor and fill it into the cache struct.
874 if (updateCache) {
875 vertexCoordinateArray.clear();
876 vertexCoordinateArray.addPath(path, curveInverseScale: inverseScale, outline: false);
877 int vertexCount = vertexCoordinateArray.vertexCount();
878 int floatSizeInBytes = vertexCount * 2 * sizeof(float);
879 cache->vertexCount = vertexCount;
880 cache->indexCount = 0;
881 cache->primitiveType = GL_TRIANGLE_FAN;
882 cache->iscale = inverseScale;
883#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
884 funcs.glGenBuffers(1, &cache->vbo);
885 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, cache->vbo);
886 funcs.glBufferData(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, floatSizeInBytes, vertexCoordinateArray.data(), GL_STATIC_DRAW);
887 cache->ibo = 0;
888#else
889 cache->vertices = (float *) malloc(size: floatSizeInBytes);
890 memcpy(dest: cache->vertices, src: vertexCoordinateArray.data(), n: floatSizeInBytes);
891 cache->indices = nullptr;
892#endif
893 }
894
895 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: currentBrush.isOpaque());
896#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
897 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, cache->vbo);
898 uploadData(QT_VERTEX_COORD_ATTR, 0, cache->vertexCount);
899 setVertexAttributePointer(QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, 0);
900#else
901 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: cache->vertices, count: cache->vertexCount * 2);
902#endif
903 funcs.glDrawArrays(mode: cache->primitiveType, first: 0, count: cache->vertexCount);
904
905 } else {
906 // printf(" - Marking path as cachable...\n");
907 // Tag it for later so that if the same path is drawn twice, it is assumed to be static and thus cachable
908 path.makeCacheable();
909 vertexCoordinateArray.clear();
910 vertexCoordinateArray.addPath(path, curveInverseScale: inverseScale, outline: false);
911 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: currentBrush.isOpaque());
912 drawVertexArrays(vertexArray&: vertexCoordinateArray, GL_TRIANGLE_FAN);
913 }
914
915 } else {
916 bool useCache = path.isCacheable();
917 if (useCache) {
918 QRectF bbox = path.controlPointRect();
919 // If the path doesn't fit within these limits, it is possible that the triangulation will fail.
920 useCache &= (bbox.left() > -0x8000 * inverseScale)
921 && (bbox.right() < 0x8000 * inverseScale)
922 && (bbox.top() > -0x8000 * inverseScale)
923 && (bbox.bottom() < 0x8000 * inverseScale);
924 }
925
926 if (useCache) {
927 QVectorPath::CacheEntry *data = path.lookupCacheData(engine: q);
928 QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache *cache;
929
930 bool updateCache = false;
931
932 if (data) {
933 cache = (QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache *) data->data;
934 // Check if scale factor is exceeded and regenerate if so...
935 qreal scaleFactor = cache->iscale / inverseScale;
936 if (scaleFactor < 0.5 || scaleFactor > 2.0) {
937#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
938 glDeleteBuffers(1, &cache->vbo);
939 glDeleteBuffers(1, &cache->ibo);
940#else
941 free(ptr: cache->vertices);
942 free(ptr: cache->indices);
943#endif
944 updateCache = true;
945 }
946 } else {
947 cache = new QOpenGL2PEVectorPathCache;
948 data = const_cast<QVectorPath &>(path).addCacheData(engine: q, data: cache, cleanup: cleanupVectorPath);
949 updateCache = true;
950 }
951
952 // Flatten the path at the current scale factor and fill it into the cache struct.
953 if (updateCache) {
954 QTriangleSet polys = qTriangulate(path, matrix: QTransform().scale(sx: 1 / inverseScale, sy: 1 / inverseScale), lod: 1, allowUintIndices: supportsElementIndexUint);
955 cache->vertexCount = polys.vertices.size() / 2;
956 cache->indexCount = polys.indices.size();
957 cache->primitiveType = GL_TRIANGLES;
958 cache->iscale = inverseScale;
959 cache->indexType = polys.indices.type();
960#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
961 funcs.glGenBuffers(1, &cache->vbo);
962 funcs.glGenBuffers(1, &cache->ibo);
963 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, cache->vbo);
964 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, cache->ibo);
965
966 if (polys.indices.type() == QVertexIndexVector::UnsignedInt)
967 funcs.glBufferData(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, sizeof(quint32) * polys.indices.size(), polys.indices.data(), GL_STATIC_DRAW);
968 else
969 funcs.glBufferData(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, sizeof(quint16) * polys.indices.size(), polys.indices.data(), GL_STATIC_DRAW);
970
971 QVarLengthArray<float> vertices(polys.vertices.size());
972 for (int i = 0; i < polys.vertices.size(); ++i)
973 vertices[i] = float(inverseScale * polys.vertices.at(i));
974 funcs.glBufferData(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, sizeof(float) * vertices.size(), vertices.data(), GL_STATIC_DRAW);
975#else
976 cache->vertices = (float *) malloc(size: sizeof(float) * polys.vertices.size());
977 if (polys.indices.type() == QVertexIndexVector::UnsignedInt) {
978 cache->indices = (quint32 *) malloc(size: sizeof(quint32) * polys.indices.size());
979 memcpy(dest: cache->indices, src: polys.indices.data(), n: sizeof(quint32) * polys.indices.size());
980 } else {
981 cache->indices = (quint16 *) malloc(size: sizeof(quint16) * polys.indices.size());
982 memcpy(dest: cache->indices, src: polys.indices.data(), n: sizeof(quint16) * polys.indices.size());
983 }
984 for (int i = 0; i < polys.vertices.size(); ++i)
985 cache->vertices[i] = float(inverseScale * polys.vertices.at(i));
986#endif
987 }
988
989 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: currentBrush.isOpaque());
990#ifdef QT_OPENGL_CACHE_AS_VBOS
991 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, cache->vbo);
992 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, cache->ibo);
993 uploadData(QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, 0, cache->vertexCount);
994 setVertexAttributePointer(QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, 0);
995 if (cache->indexType == QVertexIndexVector::UnsignedInt)
996 funcs.glDrawElements(cache->primitiveType, cache->indexCount, GL_UNSIGNED_INT, 0);
997 else
998 funcs.glDrawElements(cache->primitiveType, cache->indexCount, GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, 0);
999 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, 0);
1000 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, 0);
1001#else
1002 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: cache->vertices, count: cache->vertexCount * 2);
1003 const GLenum indexValueType = cache->indexType == QVertexIndexVector::UnsignedInt ? GL_UNSIGNED_INT : GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
1004 const bool useIndexVbo = uploadIndexData(data: cache->indices, indexValueType, count: cache->indexCount);
1005 funcs.glDrawElements(mode: cache->primitiveType, count: cache->indexCount, type: indexValueType, indices: useIndexVbo ? nullptr : cache->indices);
1006#endif
1007
1008 } else {
1009 // printf(" - Marking path as cachable...\n");
1010 // Tag it for later so that if the same path is drawn twice, it is assumed to be static and thus cachable
1011 path.makeCacheable();
1012
1013 if (device->context()->format().stencilBufferSize() <= 0) {
1014 // If there is no stencil buffer, triangulate the path instead.
1015
1016 QRectF bbox = path.controlPointRect();
1017 // If the path doesn't fit within these limits, it is possible that the triangulation will fail.
1018 bool withinLimits = (bbox.left() > -0x8000 * inverseScale)
1019 && (bbox.right() < 0x8000 * inverseScale)
1020 && (bbox.top() > -0x8000 * inverseScale)
1021 && (bbox.bottom() < 0x8000 * inverseScale);
1022 if (withinLimits) {
1023 QTriangleSet polys = qTriangulate(path, matrix: QTransform().scale(sx: 1 / inverseScale, sy: 1 / inverseScale), lod: 1, allowUintIndices: supportsElementIndexUint);
1024
1025 QVarLengthArray<float> vertices(polys.vertices.size());
1026 for (int i = 0; i < polys.vertices.size(); ++i)
1027 vertices[i] = float(inverseScale * polys.vertices.at(i));
1028
1029 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: currentBrush.isOpaque());
1030 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: vertices.constData(), count: vertices.size());
1031 const GLenum indexValueType = funcs.hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::ElementIndexUint) ? GL_UNSIGNED_INT : GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
1032 const bool useIndexVbo = uploadIndexData(data: polys.indices.data(), indexValueType, count: polys.indices.size());
1033 funcs.glDrawElements(GL_TRIANGLES, count: polys.indices.size(), type: indexValueType, indices: useIndexVbo ? nullptr : polys.indices.data());
1034 } else {
1035 // We can't handle big, concave painter paths with OpenGL without stencil buffer.
1036 qWarning(msg: "Painter path exceeds +/-32767 pixels.");
1037 }
1038 return;
1039 }
1040
1041 // The path is too complicated & needs the stencil technique
1042 vertexCoordinateArray.clear();
1043 vertexCoordinateArray.addPath(path, curveInverseScale: inverseScale, outline: false);
1044
1045 fillStencilWithVertexArray(vertexArray&: vertexCoordinateArray, useWindingFill: path.hasWindingFill());
1046
1047 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0xff);
1048 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_REPLACE, GL_REPLACE);
1049
1050 if (q->state()->clipTestEnabled) {
1051 // Pass when high bit is set, replace stencil value with current clip
1052 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_NOTEQUAL, ref: q->state()->currentClip, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1053 } else if (path.hasWindingFill()) {
1054 // Pass when any bit is set, replace stencil value with 0
1055 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_NOTEQUAL, ref: 0, mask: 0xff);
1056 } else {
1057 // Pass when high bit is set, replace stencil value with 0
1058 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_NOTEQUAL, ref: 0, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1059 }
1060 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: currentBrush.isOpaque());
1061
1062 // Stencil the brush onto the dest buffer
1063 composite(boundingRect: vertexCoordinateArray.boundingRect());
1064 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0);
1065 updateClipScissorTest();
1066 }
1067 }
1068}
1069
1070
1071void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::fillStencilWithVertexArray(const float *data,
1072 int count,
1073 int *stops,
1074 int stopCount,
1075 const QOpenGLRect &bounds,
1076 StencilFillMode mode)
1077{
1078 Q_ASSERT(count || stops);
1079
1080// qDebug("QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::fillStencilWithVertexArray()");
1081 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0xff); // Enable stencil writes
1082
1083 if (dirtyStencilRegion.intersects(r: currentScissorBounds)) {
1084 const QRegion clearRegion = dirtyStencilRegion.intersected(r: currentScissorBounds);
1085 funcs.glClearStencil(s: 0); // Clear to zero
1086 for (const QRect &rect : clearRegion) {
1087#ifndef QT_GL_NO_SCISSOR_TEST
1088 setScissor(rect);
1089#endif
1090 funcs.glClear(GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT);
1091 }
1092
1093 dirtyStencilRegion -= currentScissorBounds;
1094
1095#ifndef QT_GL_NO_SCISSOR_TEST
1096 updateClipScissorTest();
1097#endif
1098 }
1099
1100 funcs.glColorMask(GL_FALSE, GL_FALSE, GL_FALSE, GL_FALSE); // Disable color writes
1101 useSimpleShader();
1102#ifndef QT_NO_DEBUG
1103 if (ctx->format().stencilBufferSize() <= 0)
1104 qWarning("OpenGL paint engine: attempted to use stencil test without requesting a stencil buffer.");
1105#endif
1106 funcs.glEnable(GL_STENCIL_TEST); // For some reason, this has to happen _after_ the simple shader is use()'d
1107
1108 if (mode == WindingFillMode) {
1109 Q_ASSERT(stops && !count);
1110 if (q->state()->clipTestEnabled) {
1111 // Flatten clip values higher than current clip, and set high bit to match current clip
1112 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT | q->state()->currentClip, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1113 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_REPLACE, GL_REPLACE);
1114 composite(boundingRect: bounds);
1115
1116 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_EQUAL, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1117 } else if (!stencilClean) {
1118 // Clear stencil buffer within bounding rect
1119 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_ALWAYS, ref: 0, mask: 0xff);
1120 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_ZERO, GL_ZERO, GL_ZERO);
1121 composite(boundingRect: bounds);
1122 }
1123
1124 // Inc. for front-facing triangle
1125 funcs.glStencilOpSeparate(GL_FRONT, GL_KEEP, GL_INCR_WRAP, GL_INCR_WRAP);
1126 // Dec. for back-facing "holes"
1127 funcs.glStencilOpSeparate(GL_BACK, GL_KEEP, GL_DECR_WRAP, GL_DECR_WRAP);
1128 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1129 drawVertexArrays(data, stops, stopCount, GL_TRIANGLE_FAN);
1130
1131 if (q->state()->clipTestEnabled) {
1132 // Clear high bit of stencil outside of path
1133 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_EQUAL, ref: q->state()->currentClip, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1134 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_REPLACE, GL_REPLACE);
1135 funcs.glStencilMask(GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1136 composite(boundingRect: bounds);
1137 }
1138 } else if (mode == OddEvenFillMode) {
1139 funcs.glStencilMask(GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1140 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_KEEP, GL_INVERT); // Simply invert the stencil bit
1141 drawVertexArrays(data, stops, stopCount, GL_TRIANGLE_FAN);
1142
1143 } else { // TriStripStrokeFillMode
1144 Q_ASSERT(count && !stops); // tristrips generated directly, so no vertexArray or stops
1145 funcs.glStencilMask(GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1146#if 0
1147 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_KEEP, GL_INVERT); // Simply invert the stencil bit
1148 setVertexAttributePointer(QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data);
1149 funcs.glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP, 0, count);
1150#else
1151
1152 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_KEEP, GL_REPLACE);
1153 if (q->state()->clipTestEnabled) {
1154 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, ref: q->state()->currentClip | GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT,
1155 mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1156 } else {
1157 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_ALWAYS, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT, mask: 0xff);
1158 }
1159
1160 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data, count: count * 2);
1161 funcs.glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP, first: 0, count);
1162#endif
1163 }
1164
1165 // Enable color writes & disable stencil writes
1166 funcs.glColorMask(GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE);
1167}
1168
1169/*
1170 If the maximum value in the stencil buffer is GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT - 1,
1171 restore the stencil buffer to a pristine state. The current clip region
1172 is set to 1, and the rest to 0.
1173*/
1174void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::resetClipIfNeeded()
1175{
1176 if (maxClip != (GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT - 1))
1177 return;
1178
1179 Q_Q(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
1180
1181 useSimpleShader();
1182 funcs.glEnable(GL_STENCIL_TEST);
1183 funcs.glColorMask(GL_FALSE, GL_FALSE, GL_FALSE, GL_FALSE);
1184
1185 QRectF bounds = q->state()->matrix.inverted().mapRect(QRectF(0, 0, width, height));
1186 QOpenGLRect rect(bounds.left(), bounds.top(), bounds.right(), bounds.bottom());
1187
1188 // Set high bit on clip region
1189 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, ref: q->state()->currentClip, mask: 0xff);
1190 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_INVERT, GL_INVERT);
1191 funcs.glStencilMask(GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1192 composite(boundingRect: rect);
1193
1194 // Reset clipping to 1 and everything else to zero
1195 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_NOTEQUAL, ref: 0x01, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1196 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_ZERO, GL_REPLACE, GL_REPLACE);
1197 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0xff);
1198 composite(boundingRect: rect);
1199
1200 q->state()->currentClip = 1;
1201 q->state()->canRestoreClip = false;
1202
1203 maxClip = 1;
1204
1205 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0x0);
1206 funcs.glColorMask(GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE, GL_TRUE);
1207}

1209bool QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::prepareForCachedGlyphDraw(const QFontEngineGlyphCache &cache)
1210{
1211 Q_Q(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
1212
1213 Q_ASSERT(cache.transform().type() <= QTransform::TxScale);
1214
1215 QTransform &transform = q->state()->matrix;
1216 transform.scale(sx: 1.0 / cache.transform().m11(), sy: 1.0 / cache.transform().m22());
1217 bool ret = prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: false);
1218 transform.scale(sx: cache.transform().m11(), sy: cache.transform().m22());
1219
1220 return ret;
1221}
1222
1223bool QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::prepareForDraw(bool srcPixelsAreOpaque)
1224{
1225 if (brushTextureDirty && (mode == TextDrawingMode || mode == BrushDrawingMode))
1226 updateBrushTexture();
1227
1228 if (compositionModeDirty)
1229 updateCompositionMode();
1230
1231 if (matrixDirty)
1232 updateMatrix();
1233
1234 const bool stateHasOpacity = q->state()->opacity < 0.99f;
1235 if (q->state()->composition_mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source
1236 || (q->state()->composition_mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver
1237 && srcPixelsAreOpaque && !stateHasOpacity))
1238 {
1239 funcs.glDisable(GL_BLEND);
1240 } else {
1241 funcs.glEnable(GL_BLEND);
1242 }
1243
1244 QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::OpacityMode opacityMode;
1245 if (mode == ImageOpacityArrayDrawingMode) {
1246 opacityMode = QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::AttributeOpacity;
1247 } else {
1248 opacityMode = stateHasOpacity ? QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::UniformOpacity
1249 : QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::NoOpacity;
1250 if (stateHasOpacity && (mode != ImageDrawingMode && mode != ImageArrayDrawingMode)) {
1251 // Using a brush
1252 bool brushIsPattern = (currentBrush.style() >= Qt::Dense1Pattern) &&
1253 (currentBrush.style() <= Qt::DiagCrossPattern);
1254
1255 if ((currentBrush.style() == Qt::SolidPattern) || brushIsPattern)
1256 opacityMode = QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::NoOpacity; // Global opacity handled by srcPixel shader
1257 }
1258 }
1259 shaderManager->setOpacityMode(opacityMode);
1260
1261 bool changed = shaderManager->useCorrectShaderProg();
1262 // If the shader program needs changing, we change it and mark all uniforms as dirty
1263 if (changed) {
1264 // The shader program has changed so mark all uniforms as dirty:
1265 brushUniformsDirty = true;
1266 opacityUniformDirty = true;
1267 matrixUniformDirty = true;
1268 }
1269
1270 if (brushUniformsDirty && (mode == TextDrawingMode || mode == BrushDrawingMode))
1271 updateBrushUniforms();
1272
1273 if (opacityMode == QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::UniformOpacity && opacityUniformDirty) {
1274 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::GlobalOpacity), value: (GLfloat)q->state()->opacity);
1275 opacityUniformDirty = false;
1276 }
1277
1278 if (matrixUniformDirty && shaderManager->hasComplexGeometry()) {
1279 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::Matrix),
1280 value: pmvMatrix);
1281 matrixUniformDirty = false;
1282 }
1283
1284 return changed;
1285}

1287void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::composite(const QOpenGLRect& boundingRect)
1288{
1289 setCoords(coords: staticVertexCoordinateArray, rect: boundingRect);
1290
1291 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: staticVertexCoordinateArray, count: 8);
1292 funcs.glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLE_FAN, first: 0, count: 4);
1293}

1295// Draws the vertex array as a set of <vertexArrayStops.size()> triangle fans.
1296void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::drawVertexArrays(const float *data, int *stops, int stopCount,
1297 GLenum primitive)
1298{
1299 // Now setup the pointer to the vertex array:
1300 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data, count: stops[stopCount-1] * 2);
1301
1302 int previousStop = 0;
1303 for (int i=0; i<stopCount; ++i) {
1304 int stop = stops[i];
1305
1306 funcs.glDrawArrays(mode: primitive, first: previousStop, count: stop - previousStop);
1307 previousStop = stop;
1308 }
1309}

1356
1357void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::stroke(const QVectorPath &path, const QPen &pen)
1358{
1359 const QOpenGL2PaintEngineState *s = q->state();
1360 if (snapToPixelGrid) {
1361 snapToPixelGrid = false;
1362 matrixDirty = true;
1363 }
1364
1365 const Qt::PenStyle penStyle = qpen_style(p: pen);
1366 const QBrush &penBrush = qpen_brush(p: pen);
1367 const bool opaque = penBrush.isOpaque() && s->opacity > 0.99;
1368
1369 transferMode(newMode: BrushDrawingMode);
1370
1371 // updateMatrix() is responsible for setting the inverse scale on
1372 // the strokers, so we need to call it here and not wait for
1373 // prepareForDraw() down below.
1374 updateMatrix();
1375
1376 QRectF clip = q->state()->matrix.inverted().mapRect(q->state()->clipEnabled
1377 ? q->state()->rectangleClip
1378 : QRectF(0, 0, width, height));
1379
1380 if (penStyle == Qt::SolidLine) {
1381 stroker.process(path, pen, clip, hints: s->renderHints);
1382
1383 } else { // Some sort of dash
1384 dasher.process(path, pen, clip, hints: s->renderHints);
1385
1386 QVectorPath dashStroke(dasher.points(),
1387 dasher.elementCount(),
1388 dasher.elementTypes());
1389 stroker.process(path: dashStroke, pen, clip, hints: s->renderHints);
1390 }
1391
1392 if (!stroker.vertexCount())
1393 return;
1394
1395 if (opaque) {
1396 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: opaque);
1397
1398 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: stroker.vertices(), count: stroker.vertexCount());
1399 funcs.glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP, first: 0, count: stroker.vertexCount() / 2);
1400 } else {
1401 qreal width = qpen_widthf(p: pen) / 2;
1402 if (width == 0)
1403 width = 0.5;
1404 qreal extra = pen.joinStyle() == Qt::MiterJoin
1405 ? qMax(a: pen.miterLimit() * width, b: width)
1406 : width;
1407
1408 if (pen.isCosmetic())
1409 extra = extra * inverseScale;
1410
1411 QRectF bounds = path.controlPointRect().adjusted(xp1: -extra, yp1: -extra, xp2: extra, yp2: extra);
1412
1413 fillStencilWithVertexArray(data: stroker.vertices(), count: stroker.vertexCount() / 2,
1414 stops: nullptr, stopCount: 0, bounds, mode: QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::TriStripStrokeFillMode);
1415
1416 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_REPLACE, GL_REPLACE);
1417
1418 // Pass when any bit is set, replace stencil value with 0
1419 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_NOTEQUAL, ref: 0, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
1420 prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: false);
1421
1422 // Stencil the brush onto the dest buffer
1423 composite(boundingRect: bounds);
1424
1425 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0);
1426
1427 updateClipScissorTest();
1428 }
1429}

1497void QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::drawPixmap(const QRectF& dest, const QPixmap & pixmap, const QRectF & src)
1498{
1499 Q_D(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
1500 QOpenGLContext *ctx = d->ctx;
1501
1502 // Draw pixmaps that are really images as images since drawImage has
1503 // better handling of non-default image formats.
1504 if (pixmap.paintEngine()->type() == QPaintEngine::Raster && !pixmap.isQBitmap())
1505 return drawImage(r: dest, pm: pixmap.toImage(), sr: src);
1506
1507 int max_texture_size = ctx->d_func()->maxTextureSize();
1508 if (pixmap.width() > max_texture_size || pixmap.height() > max_texture_size) {
1509 QPixmap scaled = pixmap.scaled(w: max_texture_size, h: max_texture_size, aspectMode: Qt::KeepAspectRatio);
1510
1511 const qreal sx = scaled.width() / qreal(pixmap.width());
1512 const qreal sy = scaled.height() / qreal(pixmap.height());
1513
1514 drawPixmap(dest, pixmap: scaled, src: scaleRect(r: src, sx, sy));
1515 return;
1516 }
1517
1518 ensureActive();
1519 d->transferMode(newMode: ImageDrawingMode);
1520
1521 GLenum filterMode = state()->renderHints & QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform ? GL_LINEAR : GL_NEAREST;
1522 d->updateTexture(QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT, texture: pixmap, GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE, filterMode);
1523
1524 bool isBitmap = pixmap.isQBitmap();
1525 bool isOpaque = !isBitmap && !pixmap.hasAlpha();
1526
1527 d->shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(isBitmap ? QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::PatternSrc : QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageSrc);
1528
1529 QOpenGLRect srcRect(src.left(), src.top(), src.right(), src.bottom());
1530 d->drawTexture(dest, src: srcRect, textureSize: pixmap.size(), opaque: isOpaque, pattern: isBitmap);
1531}
1532
1533void QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::drawImage(const QRectF& dest, const QImage& image, const QRectF& src,
1534 Qt::ImageConversionFlags)
1535{
1536 Q_D(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
1537 QOpenGLContext *ctx = d->ctx;
1538
1539 int max_texture_size = ctx->d_func()->maxTextureSize();
1540 if (image.width() > max_texture_size || image.height() > max_texture_size) {
1541 QImage scaled = image.scaled(w: max_texture_size, h: max_texture_size, aspectMode: Qt::KeepAspectRatio);
1542
1543 const qreal sx = scaled.width() / qreal(image.width());
1544 const qreal sy = scaled.height() / qreal(image.height());
1545
1546 drawImage(dest, image: scaled, src: scaleRect(r: src, sx, sy));
1547 return;
1548 }
1549
1550 ensureActive();
1551 d->transferMode(newMode: ImageDrawingMode);
1552
1553 QOpenGLTextureUploader::BindOptions bindOption = QOpenGLTextureUploader::PremultipliedAlphaBindOption;
1554 // Use specialized bind for formats we have specialized shaders for.
1555 switch (image.format()) {
1556 case QImage::Format_RGBA8888:
1557 case QImage::Format_ARGB32:
1558 case QImage::Format_RGBA64:
1559 case QImage::Format_RGBA16FPx4:
1560 case QImage::Format_RGBA32FPx4:
1561 d->shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::NonPremultipliedImageSrc);
1562 bindOption = { };
1563 break;
1564 case QImage::Format_Alpha8:
1565 if (ctx->functions()->hasOpenGLFeature(feature: QOpenGLFunctions::TextureRGFormats)) {
1566 d->shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::AlphaImageSrc);
1567 bindOption = QOpenGLTextureUploader::UseRedForAlphaAndLuminanceBindOption;
1568 } else
1569 d->shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageSrc);
1570 break;
1571 case QImage::Format_Grayscale8:
1572 case QImage::Format_Grayscale16:
1573 if (ctx->functions()->hasOpenGLFeature(feature: QOpenGLFunctions::TextureRGFormats)) {
1574 d->shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::GrayscaleImageSrc);
1575 bindOption = QOpenGLTextureUploader::UseRedForAlphaAndLuminanceBindOption;
1576 } else
1577 d->shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageSrc);
1578 break;
1579 default:
1580 d->shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageSrc);
1581 break;
1582 }
1583
1584 ImageWithBindOptions imageWithOptions = { .image: image, .options: bindOption };
1585 GLenum filterMode = state()->renderHints & QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform ? GL_LINEAR : GL_NEAREST;
1586 d->updateTexture(QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT, texture: imageWithOptions, GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE, filterMode);
1587
1588 d->drawTexture(dest, src, textureSize: image.size(), opaque: !image.hasAlphaChannel());
1589}

1638void QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::drawTextItem(const QPointF &p, const QTextItem &textItem)
1639{
1640 Q_D(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
1641
1642 ensureActive();
1643 QOpenGL2PaintEngineState *s = state();
1644
1645 const QTextItemInt &ti = static_cast<const QTextItemInt &>(textItem);
1646
1647 QTransform::TransformationType txtype = s->matrix.type();
1648
1649 QFontEngine::GlyphFormat glyphFormat = ti.fontEngine->glyphFormat != QFontEngine::Format_None
1650 ? ti.fontEngine->glyphFormat : d->glyphCacheFormat;
1651
1652 if (glyphFormat == QFontEngine::Format_A32) {
1653 if (d->device->context()->format().alphaBufferSize() > 0 || txtype > QTransform::TxTranslate
1654 || (state()->composition_mode != QPainter::CompositionMode_Source
1655 && state()->composition_mode != QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver))
1656 {
1657 glyphFormat = QFontEngine::Format_A8;
1658 }
1659 }
1660
1661 if (shouldDrawCachedGlyphs(ti.fontEngine, s->matrix)) {
1662 QVarLengthArray<QFixedPoint> positions;
1663 QVarLengthArray<glyph_t> glyphs;
1664 QTransform matrix = QTransform::fromTranslate(dx: p.x(), dy: p.y());
1665 ti.fontEngine->getGlyphPositions(glyphs: ti.glyphs, matrix, flags: ti.flags, glyphs_out&: glyphs, positions);
1666
1667 {
1668 QStaticTextItem staticTextItem;
1669 staticTextItem.setFontEngine(ti.fontEngine);
1670 staticTextItem.glyphs = glyphs.data();
1671 staticTextItem.numGlyphs = glyphs.size();
1672 staticTextItem.glyphPositions = positions.data();
1673
1674 d->drawCachedGlyphs(glyphFormat, staticTextItem: &staticTextItem);
1675 }
1676 return;
1677 }
1678
1679 QPaintEngineEx::drawTextItem(p, textItem: ti);
1680}

1688 : QStaticTextUserData(OpenGLUserData), cacheSize(0, 0), cacheSerialNumber(0)
1689 {
1690 }
1691
1692 ~QOpenGLStaticTextUserData()
1693 {
1694 }

1697 QOpenGL2PEXVertexArray vertexCoordinateArray;
1698 QOpenGL2PEXVertexArray textureCoordinateArray;
1699 QFontEngine::GlyphFormat glyphFormat;
1700 int cacheSerialNumber;
1701 };

1706// #define QT_OPENGL_DRAWCACHEDGLYPHS_INDEX_ARRAY_VBO
1707
1708bool QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::shouldDrawCachedGlyphs(QFontEngine *fontEngine, const QTransform &t) const
1709{
1710 // The paint engine does not support projected cached glyph drawing
1711 if (t.type() == QTransform::TxProject)
1712 return false;
1713
1714 // The font engine might not support filling the glyph cache
1715 // with the given transform applied, in which case we need to
1716 // fall back to the QPainterPath code-path.
1717 if (!fontEngine->supportsTransformation(transform: t)) {
1718 // Except that drawing paths is slow, so for scales between
1719 // 0.5 and 2.0 we leave the glyph cache untransformed and deal
1720 // with the transform ourselves when painting, resulting in
1721 // drawing 1x cached glyphs with a smooth-scale.
1722 float det = t.determinant();
1723 if (det >= 0.25f && det <= 4.f) {
1724 // Assuming the baseclass still agrees
1725 return QPaintEngineEx::shouldDrawCachedGlyphs(fontEngine, m: t);
1726 }
1727
1728 return false; // Fall back to path-drawing
1729 }
1730
1731 return QPaintEngineEx::shouldDrawCachedGlyphs(fontEngine, m: t);
1732}
1733
1734
1735// MSVC 19.28 does show spurious warning "C4723: potential divide by 0" for the code
1736// that divides by QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache::height() in release builds.
1737// Anyhow, the code path in this method is only executed
1738// if height() != 0. Therefore disable the warning.
1739QT_WARNING_PUSH
1740QT_WARNING_DISABLE_MSVC(4723)
1741
1742void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::drawCachedGlyphs(QFontEngine::GlyphFormat glyphFormat,
1743 QStaticTextItem *staticTextItem)
1744{
1745 Q_Q(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
1746
1747 QOpenGL2PaintEngineState *s = q->state();
1748
1749 void *cacheKey = ctx; // use context, not the shareGroup() -> the GL glyph cache uses FBOs which may not be shareable
1750 bool recreateVertexArrays = false;
1751
1752 QTransform glyphCacheTransform;
1753 QFontEngine *fe = staticTextItem->fontEngine();
1754 if (fe->supportsTransformation(transform: s->matrix)) {
1755 // The font-engine supports rendering glyphs with the current transform, so we
1756 // build a glyph-cache with the scale pre-applied, so that the cache contains
1757 // glyphs with the appropriate resolution in the case of retina displays.
1758 glyphCacheTransform = s->matrix.type() < QTransform::TxRotate ?
1759 QTransform::fromScale(dx: qAbs(t: s->matrix.m11()), dy: qAbs(t: s->matrix.m22())) :
1760 QTransform::fromScale(
1761 dx: QVector2D(s->matrix.m11(), s->matrix.m12()).length(),
1762 dy: QVector2D(s->matrix.m21(), s->matrix.m22()).length());
1763 }
1764
1765 QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache *cache =
1766 (QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache *) fe->glyphCache(key: cacheKey, format: glyphFormat, transform: glyphCacheTransform);
1767 if (!cache || cache->glyphFormat() != glyphFormat || cache->contextGroup() == nullptr) {
1768 cache = new QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache(glyphFormat, glyphCacheTransform);
1769 fe->setGlyphCache(key: cacheKey, data: cache);
1770 recreateVertexArrays = true;
1771 }
1772
1773 if (staticTextItem->userDataNeedsUpdate) {
1774 recreateVertexArrays = true;
1775 } else if (staticTextItem->userData() == nullptr) {
1776 recreateVertexArrays = true;
1777 } else if (staticTextItem->userData()->type != QStaticTextUserData::OpenGLUserData) {
1778 recreateVertexArrays = true;
1779 } else {
1780 QOpenGLStaticTextUserData *userData = static_cast<QOpenGLStaticTextUserData *>(staticTextItem->userData());
1781 if (userData->glyphFormat != glyphFormat) {
1782 recreateVertexArrays = true;
1783 } else if (userData->cacheSerialNumber != cache->serialNumber()) {
1784 recreateVertexArrays = true;
1785 }
1786 }
1787
1788 // We only need to update the cache with new glyphs if we are actually going to recreate the vertex arrays.
1789 // If the cache size has changed, we do need to regenerate the vertices, but we don't need to repopulate the
1790 // cache so this text is performed before we test if the cache size has changed.
1791 if (recreateVertexArrays) {
1792 cache->setPaintEnginePrivate(this);
1793 if (!cache->populate(fontEngine: fe, numGlyphs: staticTextItem->numGlyphs,
1794 glyphs: staticTextItem->glyphs, positions: staticTextItem->glyphPositions,
1795 renderHints: s->renderHints)) {
1796 // No space for glyphs in cache. We need to reset it and try again.
1797 cache->clear();
1798 cache->populate(fontEngine: fe, numGlyphs: staticTextItem->numGlyphs,
1799 glyphs: staticTextItem->glyphs, positions: staticTextItem->glyphPositions,
1800 renderHints: s->renderHints);
1801 }
1802
1803 if (cache->hasPendingGlyphs()) {
1804 // Filling in the glyphs binds and sets parameters, so we need to
1805 // ensure that the glyph cache doesn't mess with whatever unit
1806 // is currently active. Note that the glyph cache internally
1807 // uses the image texture unit for blitting to the cache, while
1808 // we switch between image and mask units when drawing.
1809 static const GLenum glypchCacheTextureUnit = QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT;
1810 activateTextureUnit(textureUnit: glypchCacheTextureUnit);
1811
1812 cache->fillInPendingGlyphs();
1813
1814 // We assume the cache can be trusted on which texture was bound
1815 lastTextureUsed = cache->texture();
1816
1817 // But since the brush and image texture units are possibly shared
1818 // we may have to re-bind brush textures after filling in the cache.
1819 brushTextureDirty = (QT_BRUSH_TEXTURE_UNIT == glypchCacheTextureUnit);
1820 }
1821 cache->setPaintEnginePrivate(nullptr);
1822 }
1823
1824 if (cache->width() == 0 || cache->height() == 0)
1825 return;
1826
1827 if (glyphFormat == QFontEngine::Format_ARGB)
1828 transferMode(newMode: ImageArrayDrawingMode);
1829 else
1830 transferMode(newMode: TextDrawingMode);
1831
1832 int margin = fe->glyphMargin(format: glyphFormat);
1833
1834 GLfloat dx = 1.0 / cache->width();
1835 GLfloat dy = 1.0 / cache->height();
1836
1837 // Use global arrays by default
1838 QOpenGL2PEXVertexArray *vertexCoordinates = &vertexCoordinateArray;
1839 QOpenGL2PEXVertexArray *textureCoordinates = &textureCoordinateArray;
1840
1841 if (staticTextItem->useBackendOptimizations) {
1842 QOpenGLStaticTextUserData *userData = nullptr;
1843
1844 if (staticTextItem->userData() == nullptr
1845 || staticTextItem->userData()->type != QStaticTextUserData::OpenGLUserData) {
1846
1847 userData = new QOpenGLStaticTextUserData();
1848 staticTextItem->setUserData(userData);
1849
1850 } else {
1851 userData = static_cast<QOpenGLStaticTextUserData*>(staticTextItem->userData());
1852 }
1853
1854 userData->glyphFormat = glyphFormat;
1855 userData->cacheSerialNumber = cache->serialNumber();
1856
1857 // Use cache if backend optimizations is turned on
1858 vertexCoordinates = &userData->vertexCoordinateArray;
1859 textureCoordinates = &userData->textureCoordinateArray;
1860
1861 QSize size(cache->width(), cache->height());
1862 if (userData->cacheSize != size) {
1863 recreateVertexArrays = true;
1864 userData->cacheSize = size;
1865 }
1866 }
1867
1868 if (recreateVertexArrays) {
1869 vertexCoordinates->clear();
1870 textureCoordinates->clear();
1871
1872 bool supportsSubPixelPositions = fe->supportsSubPixelPositions();
1873 bool verticalSubPixelPositions = fe->supportsVerticalSubPixelPositions()
1874 && (s->renderHints & QPainter::VerticalSubpixelPositioning) != 0;
1875 for (int i=0; i<staticTextItem->numGlyphs; ++i) {
1876 QFixedPoint subPixelPosition;
1877 if (supportsSubPixelPositions) {
1878 subPixelPosition = fe->subPixelPositionFor(position: staticTextItem->glyphPositions[i]);
1879 if (!verticalSubPixelPositions)
1880 subPixelPosition.y = 0;
1881 }
1882
1883 QTextureGlyphCache::GlyphAndSubPixelPosition glyph(staticTextItem->glyphs[i], subPixelPosition);
1884
1885 const QTextureGlyphCache::Coord &c = cache->coords[glyph];
1886 if (c.isNull())
1887 continue;
1888
1889 int x = qFloor(v: staticTextItem->glyphPositions[i].x.toReal() * cache->transform().m11()) + c.baseLineX - margin;
1890 int y = verticalSubPixelPositions
1891 ? qRound(d: staticTextItem->glyphPositions[i].y.toReal() * cache->transform().m22())
1892 : qFloor(v: staticTextItem->glyphPositions[i].y.toReal() * cache->transform().m22());
1893 y -= c.baseLineY + margin;
1894
1895 vertexCoordinates->addQuad(rect: QRectF(x, y, c.w, c.h));
1896 textureCoordinates->addQuad(rect: QRectF(c.x*dx, c.y*dy, c.w * dx, c.h * dy));
1897 }
1898
1899 staticTextItem->userDataNeedsUpdate = false;
1900 }
1901
1902 int numGlyphs = vertexCoordinates->vertexCount() / 4;
1903 if (numGlyphs == 0)
1904 return;
1905
1906 if (elementIndices.size() < numGlyphs*6) {
1907 Q_ASSERT(elementIndices.size() % 6 == 0);
1908 int j = elementIndices.size() / 6 * 4;
1909 while (j < numGlyphs*4) {
1910 elementIndices.append(t: j + 0);
1911 elementIndices.append(t: j + 0);
1912 elementIndices.append(t: j + 1);
1913 elementIndices.append(t: j + 2);
1914 elementIndices.append(t: j + 3);
1915 elementIndices.append(t: j + 3);
1916
1917 j += 4;
1918 }
1919
1920#if defined(QT_OPENGL_DRAWCACHEDGLYPHS_INDEX_ARRAY_VBO)
1921 if (elementIndicesVBOId == 0)
1922 funcs.glGenBuffers(1, &elementIndicesVBOId);
1923
1924 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, elementIndicesVBOId);
1925 funcs.glBufferData(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, elementIndices.size() * sizeof(GLushort),
1926 elementIndices.constData(), GL_STATIC_DRAW);
1927#endif
1928 } else {
1929#if defined(QT_OPENGL_DRAWCACHEDGLYPHS_INDEX_ARRAY_VBO)
1930 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, elementIndicesVBOId);
1931#endif
1932 }
1933
1934 if (glyphFormat != QFontEngine::Format_ARGB || recreateVertexArrays) {
1935 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)vertexCoordinates->data(), count: vertexCoordinates->vertexCount() * 2);
1936 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_TEXTURE_COORDS_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)textureCoordinates->data(), count: textureCoordinates->vertexCount() * 2);
1937 }
1938
1939 if (!snapToPixelGrid) {
1940 snapToPixelGrid = true;
1941 matrixDirty = true;
1942 }
1943
1944 QBrush pensBrush = q->state()->pen.brush();
1945 setBrush(pensBrush);
1946
1947 if (glyphFormat == QFontEngine::Format_A32) {
1948
1949 // Subpixel antialiasing without gamma correction
1950
1951 QPainter::CompositionMode compMode = q->state()->composition_mode;
1952 Q_ASSERT(compMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source
1953 || compMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver);
1954
1955 shaderManager->setMaskType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::SubPixelMaskPass1);
1956
1957 if (pensBrush.style() == Qt::SolidPattern) {
1958 // Solid patterns can get away with only one pass.
1959 QColor c = pensBrush.color();
1960 qreal oldOpacity = q->state()->opacity;
1961 if (compMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source) {
1962 c = qt_premultiplyColor(c, opacity: q->state()->opacity);
1963 q->state()->opacity = 1;
1964 opacityUniformDirty = true;
1965 }
1966
1967 compositionModeDirty = false; // I can handle this myself, thank you very much
1968 prepareForCachedGlyphDraw(cache: *cache);
1969
1970 // prepareForCachedGlyphDraw() have set the opacity on the current shader, so the opacity state can now be reset.
1971 if (compMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source) {
1972 q->state()->opacity = oldOpacity;
1973 opacityUniformDirty = true;
1974 }
1975
1976 funcs.glEnable(GL_BLEND);
1977 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_CONSTANT_COLOR, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR);
1978 funcs.glBlendColor(red: c.redF(), green: c.greenF(), blue: c.blueF(), alpha: c.alphaF());
1979 } else {
1980 // Other brush styles need two passes.
1981
1982 qreal oldOpacity = q->state()->opacity;
1983 if (compMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source) {
1984 q->state()->opacity = 1;
1985 opacityUniformDirty = true;
1986 pensBrush = Qt::white;
1987 setBrush(pensBrush);
1988 }
1989
1990 compositionModeDirty = false; // I can handle this myself, thank you very much
1991 prepareForCachedGlyphDraw(cache: *cache);
1992 funcs.glEnable(GL_BLEND);
1993 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ZERO, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR);
1994
1995 updateTexture(QT_MASK_TEXTURE_UNIT, texture: cache->texture(), GL_REPEAT, GL_NEAREST, updateMode: ForceUpdate);
1996
1997#if defined(QT_OPENGL_DRAWCACHEDGLYPHS_INDEX_ARRAY_VBO)
1998 funcs.glDrawElements(GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP, 6 * numGlyphs, GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, 0);
1999#else
2000 const bool useIndexVbo = uploadIndexData(data: elementIndices.data(), GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, count: 6 * numGlyphs);
2001 funcs.glDrawElements(GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP, count: 6 * numGlyphs, GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, indices: useIndexVbo ? nullptr : elementIndices.data());
2002#endif
2003
2004 shaderManager->setMaskType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::SubPixelMaskPass2);
2005
2006 if (compMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source) {
2007 q->state()->opacity = oldOpacity;
2008 opacityUniformDirty = true;
2009 pensBrush = q->state()->pen.brush();
2010 setBrush(pensBrush);
2011 }
2012
2013 compositionModeDirty = false;
2014 prepareForCachedGlyphDraw(cache: *cache);
2015 funcs.glEnable(GL_BLEND);
2016 funcs.glBlendFunc(GL_ONE, GL_ONE);
2017 }
2018 compositionModeDirty = true;
2019 } else if (glyphFormat == QFontEngine::Format_ARGB) {
2020 currentBrush = noBrush;
2021 shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageSrc);
2022 if (prepareForCachedGlyphDraw(cache: *cache))
2023 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageTexture), QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT);
2024 } else {
2025 // Grayscale/mono glyphs
2026
2027 shaderManager->setMaskType(QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::PixelMask);
2028 prepareForCachedGlyphDraw(cache: *cache);
2029 }
2030
2031 GLenum textureUnit = QT_MASK_TEXTURE_UNIT;
2032 if (glyphFormat == QFontEngine::Format_ARGB)
2033 textureUnit = QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT;
2034
2035 QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache::FilterMode filterMode = (s->matrix.type() > QTransform::TxTranslate) ?
2036 QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache::Linear : QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache::Nearest;
2037
2038 GLenum glFilterMode = filterMode == QOpenGLTextureGlyphCache::Linear ? GL_LINEAR : GL_NEAREST;
2039
2040 TextureUpdateMode updateMode = UpdateIfNeeded;
2041 if (cache->filterMode() != filterMode) {
2042 updateMode = ForceUpdate;
2043 cache->setFilterMode(filterMode);
2044 }
2045
2046 updateTexture(textureUnit, texture: cache->texture(), GL_REPEAT, filterMode: glFilterMode, updateMode);
2047
2048#if defined(QT_OPENGL_DRAWCACHEDGLYPHS_INDEX_ARRAY_VBO)
2049 funcs.glDrawElements(GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP, 6 * numGlyphs, GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, 0);
2050 funcs.glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, 0);
2051#else
2052 const bool useIndexVbo = uploadIndexData(data: elementIndices.data(), GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, count: 6 * numGlyphs);
2053 funcs.glDrawElements(GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP, count: 6 * numGlyphs, GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, indices: useIndexVbo ? nullptr : elementIndices.data());
2054#endif
2055}

2079
2080void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::drawPixmapFragments(const QPainter::PixmapFragment *fragments,
2081 int fragmentCount, const QPixmap &pixmap,
2082 QPainter::PixmapFragmentHints hints)
2083{
2084 GLfloat dx = 1.0f / pixmap.size().width();
2085 GLfloat dy = 1.0f / pixmap.size().height();
2086
2087 vertexCoordinateArray.clear();
2088 textureCoordinateArray.clear();
2089 opacityArray.reset();
2090
2091 if (snapToPixelGrid) {
2092 snapToPixelGrid = false;
2093 matrixDirty = true;
2094 }
2095
2096 bool allOpaque = true;
2097
2098 for (int i = 0; i < fragmentCount; ++i) {
2099 qreal s = 0;
2100 qreal c = 1;
2101 if (fragments[i].rotation != 0) {
2102 s = qFastSin(x: qDegreesToRadians(degrees: fragments[i].rotation));
2103 c = qFastCos(x: qDegreesToRadians(degrees: fragments[i].rotation));
2104 }
2105
2106 qreal right = 0.5 * fragments[i].scaleX * fragments[i].width;
2107 qreal bottom = 0.5 * fragments[i].scaleY * fragments[i].height;
2108 QOpenGLPoint bottomRight(right * c - bottom * s, right * s + bottom * c);
2109 QOpenGLPoint bottomLeft(-right * c - bottom * s, -right * s + bottom * c);
2110
2111 vertexCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: bottomRight.x + fragments[i].x, y: bottomRight.y + fragments[i].y);
2112 vertexCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: -bottomLeft.x + fragments[i].x, y: -bottomLeft.y + fragments[i].y);
2113 vertexCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: -bottomRight.x + fragments[i].x, y: -bottomRight.y + fragments[i].y);
2114 vertexCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: -bottomRight.x + fragments[i].x, y: -bottomRight.y + fragments[i].y);
2115 vertexCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: bottomLeft.x + fragments[i].x, y: bottomLeft.y + fragments[i].y);
2116 vertexCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: bottomRight.x + fragments[i].x, y: bottomRight.y + fragments[i].y);
2117
2118 QOpenGLRect src(fragments[i].sourceLeft * dx, fragments[i].sourceTop * dy,
2119 (fragments[i].sourceLeft + fragments[i].width) * dx,
2120 (fragments[i].sourceTop + fragments[i].height) * dy);
2121
2122 textureCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: src.right, y: src.bottom);
2123 textureCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: src.right, y: src.top);
2124 textureCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: src.left, y: src.top);
2125 textureCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: src.left, y: src.top);
2126 textureCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: src.left, y: src.bottom);
2127 textureCoordinateArray.addVertex(x: src.right, y: src.bottom);
2128
2129 qreal opacity = fragments[i].opacity * q->state()->opacity;
2130 opacityArray << opacity << opacity << opacity << opacity << opacity << opacity;
2131 allOpaque &= (opacity >= 0.99f);
2132 }
2133
2134 transferMode(newMode: ImageOpacityArrayDrawingMode);
2135
2136 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_VERTEX_COORDS_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)vertexCoordinateArray.data(), count: vertexCoordinateArray.vertexCount() * 2);
2137 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_TEXTURE_COORDS_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)textureCoordinateArray.data(), count: textureCoordinateArray.vertexCount() * 2);
2138 uploadData(arrayIndex: QT_OPACITY_ATTR, data: (GLfloat*)opacityArray.data(), count: opacityArray.size());
2139
2140 GLenum filterMode = q->state()->renderHints & QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform ? GL_LINEAR : GL_NEAREST;
2141 updateTexture(QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT, texture: pixmap, GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE, filterMode);
2142
2143 bool isBitmap = pixmap.isQBitmap();
2144 bool isOpaque = !isBitmap && (!pixmap.hasAlpha() || (hints & QPainter::OpaqueHint)) && allOpaque;
2145
2146 // Setup for texture drawing
2147 currentBrush = noBrush;
2148 shaderManager->setSrcPixelType(isBitmap ? QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::PatternSrc
2149 : QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageSrc);
2150 if (prepareForDraw(srcPixelsAreOpaque: isOpaque))
2151 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::ImageTexture), QT_IMAGE_TEXTURE_UNIT);
2152
2153 if (isBitmap) {
2154 QColor col = qt_premultiplyColor(c: q->state()->pen.color(), opacity: (GLfloat)q->state()->opacity);
2155 shaderManager->currentProgram()->setUniformValue(location: location(uniform: QOpenGLEngineShaderManager::PatternColor), color: col);
2156 }
2157
2158 funcs.glDrawArrays(GL_TRIANGLES, first: 0, count: 6 * fragmentCount);
2159}

2161bool QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::begin(QPaintDevice *pdev)
2162{
2163 Q_D(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
2164
2165 Q_ASSERT(pdev->devType() == QInternal::OpenGL);
2166 d->device = static_cast<QOpenGLPaintDevice*>(pdev);
2167
2168 if (!d->device)
2169 return false;
2170
2171 d->device->ensureActiveTarget();
2172
2173 if (d->device->context() != QOpenGLContext::currentContext() || !d->device->context()) {
2174 qWarning(msg: "QPainter::begin(): QOpenGLPaintDevice's context needs to be current");
2175 return false;
2176 }
2177
2178 if (d->ctx != QOpenGLContext::currentContext()
2179 || (d->ctx && QOpenGLContext::currentContext() && d->ctx->format() != QOpenGLContext::currentContext()->format())) {
2180 d->vertexBuffer.destroy();
2181 d->texCoordBuffer.destroy();
2182 d->opacityBuffer.destroy();
2183 d->indexBuffer.destroy();
2184 d->vao.destroy();
2185 }
2186
2187 d->ctx = QOpenGLContext::currentContext();
2188 d->ctx->d_func()->active_engine = this;
2189
2190 QOpenGLPaintDevicePrivate::get(dev: d->device)->beginPaint();
2191
2192 d->funcs.initializeOpenGLFunctions();
2193
2194 // Generate a new Vertex Array Object if we don't have one already. We can
2195 // only hit the VAO-based path when using a core profile context. This is
2196 // because while non-core contexts can support VAOs via extensions, legacy
2197 // components like the QtOpenGL module do not know about VAOs. There are
2198 // still tests for QGL-QOpenGL paint engine interoperability, so keep the
2199 // status quo for now, and avoid introducing a VAO in non-core contexts.
2200 const bool needsVAO = d->ctx->format().profile() == QSurfaceFormat::CoreProfile
2201 && d->ctx->format().version() >= qMakePair(value1: 3, value2: 2);
2202 if (needsVAO && !d->vao.isCreated()) {
2203 bool created = d->vao.create();
2204
2205 // If we managed to create it then we have a profile that supports VAOs
2206 if (created)
2207 d->vao.bind();
2208 }
2209
2210 // Generate a new Vertex Buffer Object if we don't have one already
2211 if (!d->vertexBuffer.isCreated()) {
2212 d->vertexBuffer.create();
2213 // Set its usage to StreamDraw, we will use this buffer only a few times before refilling it
2214 d->vertexBuffer.setUsagePattern(QOpenGLBuffer::StreamDraw);
2215 }
2216 if (!d->texCoordBuffer.isCreated()) {
2217 d->texCoordBuffer.create();
2218 d->texCoordBuffer.setUsagePattern(QOpenGLBuffer::StreamDraw);
2219 }
