2332void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::updateClipScissorTest()
2333{
2334 Q_Q(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
2335 if (q->state()->clipTestEnabled) {
2336#ifndef QT_NO_DEBUG
2337 if (ctx->format().stencilBufferSize() <= 0)
2338 qWarning("OpenGL paint engine: attempted to use stencil test for clipping without requesting a stencil buffer.");
2339#endif
2340 funcs.glEnable(GL_STENCIL_TEST);
2341 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, ref: q->state()->currentClip, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
2342 } else {
2343 funcs.glDisable(GL_STENCIL_TEST);
2344 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_ALWAYS, ref: 0, mask: 0xff);
2345 }
2346
2347#ifdef QT_GL_NO_SCISSOR_TEST
2348 currentScissorBounds = QRect(0, 0, width, height);
2349#else
2350 QRect bounds = q->state()->rectangleClip;
2351 if (!q->state()->clipEnabled) {
2352 if (useSystemClip)
2353 bounds = systemClip.boundingRect();
2354 else
2355 bounds = QRect(0, 0, width, height);
2356 } else {
2357 if (useSystemClip)
2358 bounds = bounds.intersected(other: systemClip.boundingRect());
2359 else
2360 bounds = bounds.intersected(other: QRect(0, 0, width, height));
2361 }
2362
2363 currentScissorBounds = bounds;
2364
2365 if (bounds == QRect(0, 0, width, height)) {
2366 funcs.glDisable(GL_SCISSOR_TEST);
2367 } else {
2368 funcs.glEnable(GL_SCISSOR_TEST);
2369 setScissor(bounds);
2370 }
2371#endif

2411void QOpenGL2PaintEngineExPrivate::writeClip(const QVectorPath &path, uint value)
2412{
2413 transferMode(newMode: BrushDrawingMode);
2414
2415 if (snapToPixelGrid) {
2416 snapToPixelGrid = false;
2417 matrixDirty = true;
2418 }
2419
2420 if (matrixDirty)
2421 updateMatrix();
2422
2423 stencilClean = false;
2424
2425 const bool singlePass = !path.hasWindingFill()
2426 && (((q->state()->currentClip == maxClip - 1) && q->state()->clipTestEnabled)
2427 || q->state()->needsClipBufferClear);
2428 const uint referenceClipValue = q->state()->needsClipBufferClear ? 1 : q->state()->currentClip;
2429
2430 if (q->state()->needsClipBufferClear)
2431 clearClip(value: 1);
2432
2433 if (path.isEmpty()) {
2434 funcs.glEnable(GL_STENCIL_TEST);
2435 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, ref: value, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
2436 return;
2437 }
2438
2439 if (q->state()->clipTestEnabled)
2440 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, ref: q->state()->currentClip, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
2441 else
2442 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_ALWAYS, ref: 0, mask: 0xff);
2443
2444 vertexCoordinateArray.clear();
2445 vertexCoordinateArray.addPath(path, curveInverseScale: inverseScale, outline: false);
2446
2447 if (!singlePass)
2448 fillStencilWithVertexArray(vertexArray&: vertexCoordinateArray, useWindingFill: path.hasWindingFill());
2449
2450 funcs.glColorMask(red: false, green: false, blue: false, alpha: false);
2451 funcs.glEnable(GL_STENCIL_TEST);
2452 useSimpleShader();
2453
2454 if (singlePass) {
2455 // Under these conditions we can set the new stencil value in a single
2456 // pass, by using the current value and the "new value" as the toggles
2457
2458 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, ref: referenceClipValue, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
2459 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_INVERT, GL_INVERT);
2460 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: value ^ referenceClipValue);
2461
2462 drawVertexArrays(vertexArray&: vertexCoordinateArray, GL_TRIANGLE_FAN);
2463 } else {
2464 funcs.glStencilOp(GL_KEEP, GL_REPLACE, GL_REPLACE);
2465 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0xff);
2466
2467 if (!q->state()->clipTestEnabled && path.hasWindingFill()) {
2468 // Pass when any clip bit is set, set high bit
2469 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_NOTEQUAL, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
2470 composite(boundingRect: vertexCoordinateArray.boundingRect());
2471 }
2472
2473 // Pass when high bit is set, replace stencil value with new clip value
2474 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_NOTEQUAL, ref: value, GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
2475
2476 composite(boundingRect: vertexCoordinateArray.boundingRect());
2477 }
2478
2479 funcs.glStencilFunc(GL_LEQUAL, ref: value, mask: ~GL_STENCIL_HIGH_BIT);
2480 funcs.glStencilMask(mask: 0);
2481
2482 funcs.glColorMask(red: true, green: true, blue: true, alpha: true);
2483}

2485void QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::clip(const QVectorPath &path, Qt::ClipOperation op)
2486{
2487// qDebug("QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::clip()");
2488 Q_D(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
2489
2490 state()->clipChanged = true;
2491
2492 ensureActive();
2493
2494 if (op == Qt::ReplaceClip) {
2495 op = Qt::IntersectClip;
2496 if (d->hasClipOperations()) {
2497 d->systemStateChanged();
2498 state()->canRestoreClip = false;
2499 }
2500 }
2501
2502#ifndef QT_GL_NO_SCISSOR_TEST
2503 if (!path.isEmpty() && op == Qt::IntersectClip && (path.shape() == QVectorPath::RectangleHint)) {
2504 const QPointF* const points = reinterpret_cast<const QPointF*>(path.points());
2505 QRectF rect(points[0], points[2]);
2506
2507 if (state()->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxScale
2508 || (state()->matrix.type() == QTransform::TxRotate
2509 && qFuzzyIsNull(d: state()->matrix.m11())
2510 && qFuzzyIsNull(d: state()->matrix.m22())))
2511 {
2512 state()->rectangleClip &= qt_mapFillRect(rect, xf: state()->matrix);
2513 d->updateClipScissorTest();
2514 return;
2515 }
2516 }
2517#endif
2518
2519 const QRect pathRect = state()->matrix.mapRect(path.controlPointRect()).toAlignedRect();
2520
2521 switch (op) {
2522 case Qt::NoClip:
2523 if (d->useSystemClip) {
2524 state()->clipTestEnabled = true;
2525 state()->currentClip = 1;
2526 } else {
2527 state()->clipTestEnabled = false;
2528 }
2529 state()->rectangleClip = QRect(0, 0, d->width, d->height);
2530 state()->canRestoreClip = false;
2531 d->updateClipScissorTest();
2532 break;
2533 case Qt::IntersectClip:
2534 state()->rectangleClip = state()->rectangleClip.intersected(other: pathRect);
2535 d->updateClipScissorTest();
2536 d->resetClipIfNeeded();
2537 ++d->maxClip;
2538 d->writeClip(path, value: d->maxClip);
2539 state()->currentClip = d->maxClip;
2540 state()->clipTestEnabled = true;
2541 break;
2542 default:
2543 break;
2544 }

2560 useSystemClip = false;

2564 //useSystemClip = widgetPrivate->extra && widgetPrivate->extra->inRenderWithPainter;

2602void QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::setState(QPainterState *new_state)
2603{
2604 // qDebug("QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx::setState()");
2605
2606 Q_D(QOpenGL2PaintEngineEx);
2607
2608 QOpenGL2PaintEngineState *s = static_cast<QOpenGL2PaintEngineState *>(new_state);
2609 QOpenGL2PaintEngineState *old_state = state();
2610
2611 QPaintEngineEx::setState(s);
2612
2613 if (s->isNew) {
2614 // Newly created state object. The call to setState()
2615 // will either be followed by a call to begin(), or we are
2616 // setting the state as part of a save().
2617 s->isNew = false;
2618 return;
2619 }
2620
2621 // Setting the state as part of a restore().
2622
2623 if (old_state == s || old_state->renderHintsChanged)
2624 renderHintsChanged();
2625
2626 if (old_state == s || old_state->matrixChanged)
2627 d->matrixDirty = true;
2628
2629 if (old_state == s || old_state->compositionModeChanged)
2630 d->compositionModeDirty = true;
2631
2632 if (old_state == s || old_state->opacityChanged)
2633 d->opacityUniformDirty = true;
2634
2635 if (old_state == s || old_state->clipChanged) {
2636 if (old_state && old_state != s && old_state->canRestoreClip) {
2637 d->updateClipScissorTest();
2638 d->funcs.glDepthFunc(GL_LEQUAL);
2639 } else {
2640 d->regenerateClip();
2641 }
2642 }
